Price: $560 OBO (Or Best Offer) (Feel free to make a reasonable offer. NO LOWBALLERS PLEASE)

Will ship (Y/N): YES - To the FFL dealer of your choice. (Buyer is responsible for all shipping fees.)

Other info: I'm the second owner. I bought this semi-auto pistol back in 2009. When I bought it, the previous owner never used it, so it was pretty much Factory New. Since it's been with me, it's only seen about 120 cartridges shot through it. After every session, it was field stripped and cleaned fully.

I never really brought it out to much as I never really got used to using it due to the increased recoil of the .40 S&W cartridge. It would throw off my aim because I was used to shooting my 9mm and .45 ACP handguns (also Glocks). With that being said, this Glock 35 never saw much range time, simply because I favored the Glock 17 and Glock 21 pistols that I own as well.

The Glock 35 has an adjustable rear sight and only includes 1 (ONE) spare magazine (it originally only came with one when I bought it). Lone Wolf Decal Grips, an extended slide release and extended magazine release have been added and it also includes a Bore Store for the pistol (altogether an $80 value). Also includes the original 'tupperware' Glock factory box it came with, along with the cleaning brush (not pictured).

Truly a marvel of engineering and easily one of the most dependable semi-auto pistol designs ever created. If you get an aftermarket barrel from a company like Lone Wolf Distributors, you can use a different caliber like 9mm. All you have to do is have the correct barrel, correct magazine and swap out the barrels to fire a different caliber altogether! No gunsmithing needed. Just drop in the parts, change the ammo and you're good to go.

Now, about the price. I'm asking $560.00 OBO for just the Glock 35, magazine and the case, cleaning brush + added 'upgrade' accessories that come with it as well as the Bore Store. 

I have extra .40 S&W ammo available at $25.00/50 Rds/Box (Winchester, 4 boxes available)

I'm not really open to any trades as I'm pretty much happy with the firearms I already own.

The set is in excellent condition, with only some minor wear on the outside of the barrel (see pics) due to being cycled and fired.

NOTE: BUYER IS RESPONSIBLE FOR ALL SHIPPING COSTS AND DROS, FFL TRANSFER FEES AND ANY OTHER UNFORESEEN FEES WHICH MAY OCCUR IN ORDER TO HAVE THE FIREARM TRANSFERRED TO THE NEW OWNER.

ANY DISTANCE FURTHER THAN THAT WILL HAVE TO BE ARRANGED AND AGREED TO BY BOTH PARTIES (SELLER AND BUYER) ALONG WITH ANY FEES OR CHARGES INCURRED, SUCH AS GASOLINE CHARGES AND BRIDGE TOLLS. I've read that there were a few "transition" models which had both when Savage changed from the lever safety to the tang safety in 1960. Smith & Wesson Model 36 (no dash) Chiefs Special - .38 S&W Special

1962 - starts at 295000
1969 - ends at 786544
1968 - diamond grips end
1966 - flat cylinder latch discontinued

I really have no idea how to rate this thing, so I tried to get some photos that would accurately represent it's condition.
